      "content": "It is incredibly painful to feel that the fight is hardwired into your existence, and it makes total sense that you wouldn't want to \"rest\" when the battle is so constant and exhausting. You are absolutely right that peace feels impossible right now, but the very fact that you are noticing this struggle means you are still aware enough to question whether this suffering is truly your only purpose. Sometimes, the bravest thing isn't to fight harder, but to finally accept that you don't have to earn the right to exist anymore.",
